International Business Machines Corp-Jakarta University Taps IBM Smarter Computing To Enhance Student Experience
Friday, 27 Apr 2012 08:01am EDT
International Business Machines Corp announced that The Sunan Kalijaga Islamic State University (UIN) Yogyakarta has adopted IBM's smarter computing approach to IT to improve the quality of the education process through highly collaborative learning services. To keep pace with the growing demands of the academic community, UIN turned to IBM Global Technology Services to build a smarter computing infrastructure. The technical goals were to streamline learning processes, improve the economics of the administration system and increase overall computing and data storage utilization. At the heart of the new infrastructure are IBM's high performance IBM BladeCenter server systems and IBM Storwize V7000 Unified Storage Systems, all integrated with the university's existing infrastructure through integration services from IBM GTS.Â 
